      "FacilityID": 44301,
      "SummaryText": "The Town of Bethlehem Wastewater Treatment Plant adheres to all applicable Federal, State and local laws pertaining to the storage of chlorine.  If an emergency were to occur, it is facility policy to evacuate personnel, and call the Albany County Emergency Response Center and request that the local Fire Department(s) to respond to the situation.  Facility personnel are not trained in the use of emergency response equipment other than personal protective equipment used while inside the chlorine storage area.\n\nThe facility is used to inject chlorine as part of the treatment process at the Town's wastewater treatment plant.  The facility complies with EPA's accident prevention rule and all applicable state and local codes and regulations as they pertain to chlorine storage and use.\n\nThe Bethlehem Department of Public Works reported that the facility has never had an incident involving chlorine which caused deaths, injuries, property or environmental damage, evacuations, or shelterings in place.\n\nIn the event of an emergency involving the on-site chlorine system, it is the policy of the Town of Bethlehem Wastewater Treatment Plant to notify the Albany County Emergency Response Center (911) and request that the local Fire Department(s) respond to the emergency."
